- **Error Handling**: When git commands hang, apply [robust-error-handling](mdc:.cursor/rules/robust-error-handling.mdc) for recovery
- **Session Management**: In session workspaces, ensure git reliability per [session-first-workflow](mdc:.cursor/rules/session-first-workflow.mdc)
- **User Experience**: Hanging commands violate [user-preferences](mdc:.cursor/rules/user-preferences.mdc) for responsiveness

## Critical Enforcement

**MANDATORY**: Any git command that could potentially hang MUST use appropriate prevention techniques from this rule.

**If a git command hangs during execution:**
1. Cancel immediately
2. Apply appropriate prevention technique  
3. Document the specific scenario in this rule if not already covered
4. Proceed with corrected command

This rule prevents workflow disruption and ensures reliable automated git operations.
